description: From Middle English stinky, stynky, equivalent to stink +‎ -y. Compare Dutch stinkig (“stinky, foul, rotten”), German stinkig (“stinky”), Hunsrik stinkich.

adjectives.description: stinky (comparative stinkier or more stinky, superlative stinkiest or most stinky)

entries.meaning: Having a strong, unpleasant smell; stinking.

examples: […]  she walked over to the table and switched off the Walkman as she sat down.
“Hey!” Nikki yelped. “That was a stinky thing to do. That was my favorite song.”

entries.meaning: (childish) a bowel movement; feces or diarrhoea
